size 8 1/2?

13:04.609 --> 13:06.437
Not the knockoffs--
the real thing.

13:06.524 --> 13:08.265
You do?!

13:08.352 --> 13:13.183
Good! Now, I'm in a situation
where money is no object,

13:13.270 --> 13:14.794
but how much...

13:14.881 --> 13:17.318
Ahh! Ohh!

13:17.405 --> 13:21.496
[whimpering]

13:21.583 --> 13:24.847
Would you put a pair aside
for me, please?

13:24.934 --> 13:26.762
Ohh!

13:26.849 --> 13:31.941
[high-pitched]: Right. Yeah,
it will make a nice surprise.

13:32.028 --> 13:33.595
-[phone rings]
-Hello.

13:33.682 --> 13:35.597
Reese?

13:35.684 --> 13:37.686
Francis, you gotta help me.

13:37.773 --> 13:40.428
I don't want
to take drugs anymore.

13:40.515 --> 13:42.430
Oh, geez.

13:42.517 --> 13:45.172
Okay, Reese, I want you
to tell me very specifically--

13:45.259 --> 13:46.869
what kind of drugs
did you take?

13:46.956 --> 13:48.871
All of them.

13:48.958 --> 13:50.655
Dude, didn't you learn anything

13:50.742 --> 13:52.570
from when my friends
baby-sat you?

13:52.657 --> 13:54.790
Remember Richie trying
to dry you off in the oven?

13:54.877 --> 13:58.620
I don't know how it happened,
but I think I did something bad.

13:58.707 --> 14:01.623
I don't know what to do.

14:01.710 --> 14:03.059
Reese, I want you to listen

14:03.146 --> 14:04.060
very carefully.

14:04.147 --> 14:05.757
You're going to be okay.

14:05.845 --> 14:07.194
I'm gonna
talk you through this.

14:07.281 --> 14:08.848
Now, the first
and most important thing

14:08.935 --> 14:10.632
you have to do is...

14:10.719 --> 14:11.938
[phone cord whips,
horse whinnies]

14:12.025 --> 14:14.201
[Reese whimpering]

14:14.288 --> 14:15.376
[whinnies]

14:15.463 --> 14:17.117
[screaming]
Hello?!

14:17.204 --> 14:19.075
Hello?

14:19.162 --> 14:20.947
[screaming]
Hello?!

14:21.034 --> 14:22.949
Okay, Jamie,
I need you to focus.

14:23.036 --> 14:24.602
You got your toy.

14:24.689 --> 14:26.953
Now take me to the stash.

14:43.491 --> 14:45.014
Here?

14:45.101 --> 14:46.494
Do we have to dig for it?

14:53.066 --> 14:54.154
Jamie, come back!

14:54.241 --> 14:55.416
You can't just go into

14:55.503 --> 14:56.808
someone else's house!

15:01.901 --> 15:03.206
Get back here!

15:03.293 --> 15:05.730
Come on, Jamie! Hurry!
Before someone sees you!

15:07.341 --> 15:08.690
I'm not kidding.

15:08.777 --> 15:10.257
You're going to get caught!

15:10.344 --> 15:12.520
MAN: See?
That's the ringleader!

15:12.607 --> 15:14.739
They've been stealing stuff
from my house all week!

15:14.826 --> 15:16.393
Every two years,
they have another baby,

15:16.480 --> 15:18.047
just so they can fit
through the window!

15:20.702 --> 15:22.312
[whistles]

15:22.399 --> 15:23.835
Hal? What are you doing here?

15:23.923 --> 15:25.228
Is everything all right?

15:25.315 --> 15:27.187
Not yet, but it will be

15:27.274 --> 15:29.319
as soon as you put these on.

15:31.104 --> 15:33.628
Are you crazy?

15:33.715 --> 15:36.631
If loving your wife is crazy,
then I'm a drooling lunatic.

15:36.718 --> 15:39.590
You deserve the moon
and the sky, Lois.

15:39.677 --> 15:40.940
Maybe someday I'll be able

15:41.027 --> 15:43.072
to buy them for you,
but for now,

15:43.159 --> 15:44.856
these will have to do.

15:44.944 --> 15:47.729
Oh, Hal.

15:47.816 --> 15:49.818
Thank you.

15:49.905 --> 15:52.952
I accidentally spent $800
on phone sex.

15:58.435 --> 16:00.524
I was doing my makeup
in the rear view mirror,

16:00.611 --> 16:02.570
and I ran over your golf clubs.

16:05.660 --> 16:09.664
I burned a hole
in your favorite dress.

16:10.752 --> 16:12.275
You didn't get that promotion

16:12.362 --> 16:14.277
because I called your boss
a fat-ass

16:14.364 --> 16:15.626
at the Christmas party.

16:17.367 --> 16:20.109
I lost my wedding ring
three years ago.

16:20.196 --> 16:22.677
This is part of a lawnmower.

16:24.984 --> 16:26.942
Your Aunt Lucy isn't angry
with you.

16:27.029 --> 16:30.032
She's dead.
I just forgot to tell you.

16:31.294 --> 16:33.731
I've read that the Chinese
invented stilts so they could

16:33.818 --> 16:35.820
survive among Panda bears.

16:35.907 --> 16:37.735
Of course, that was before
they built the Great Wall.

16:37.822 --> 16:39.215
After that, only

16:39.302 --> 16:40.956
the Emperor was allowed
to walk on them.

16:44.960 --> 16:46.701
Well, I had to do it
behind Mom's back,

16:46.788 --> 16:48.485
but I was going
through the want ads,

16:48.572 --> 16:50.748
and I finally found...

16:53.360 --> 16:56.798
That explains the 15-foot high
cloud of bourbon I was smelling.

16:57.842 --> 17:00.454
-You stole my life!
-Sam, great!

17:00.541 --> 17:02.369
I-I was just
about to call you!

17:07.590 --> 17:08.462
Oh, my God!

17:08.549 --> 17:09.680
Don't worry, Malcolm.

17:09.767 --> 17:11.726
I'll help you!

17:15.556 --> 17:17.297
Sam, you've got
to listen to me!

17:20.213 --> 17:21.953
[shouts]

17:23.172 --> 17:25.131
[yells]

17:25.218 --> 17:27.568
[panting]

17:31.137 --> 17:33.922
[whimpering]

17:35.793 --> 17:37.360
[whimpering]

17:37.447 --> 17:39.928
Hang on!

17:49.503 --> 17:50.547
[groans]

17:52.419 --> 17:53.681
Damn it!

17:53.768 --> 17:56.466
What aisle
are the screwdrivers in?

18:05.606 --> 18:06.998
Uhh! Ohh.

18:08.261 --> 18:10.480
[Malcolm panting]

18:14.049 --> 18:16.225
Which batteries
are the double A?

18:16.312 --> 18:18.967
The little ones,
or the really little ones?

18:21.056 --> 18:22.101
[whimpers]

18:23.102 --> 18:24.277
[grunts]

18:25.452 --> 18:26.540
[rapid panting]

18:26.627 --> 18:27.845
Sam, please listen...

18:27.932 --> 18:29.020
[grunts]

18:31.675 --> 18:33.721
[panting]

18:33.808 --> 18:35.026
I'm never gonna shake this guy.

18:35.114 --> 18:36.332
He's way too good.

18:36.419 --> 18:38.508
I can't outstilt him.

18:41.250 --> 18:45.036
I can't outstilt him,
but I can outskate him.

18:46.603 --> 18:49.084
[panting]

18:56.483 --> 18:58.833
Okay, your brother got
the funeral he wanted.

18:58.920 --> 19:00.791
Now let's get our $15 back.

19:05.100 --> 19:08.147
Ha! Once again,
brains triumph over...

19:12.542 --> 19:15.589
[whimpering]

19:18.505 --> 19:20.376
[whimpering
grows more frantic]

19:20.463 --> 19:22.900
[screaming]

19:28.384 --> 19:31.170
This hurts so much worse
than it looks.

19:38.916 --> 19:41.571
You're a Yankee Doodle
dead man.

19:45.836 --> 19:48.796
The weird thing is,
I always knew I'd die this way.

19:48.883 --> 19:51.277
Okay, God,
you've had your fun.

19:51.364 --> 19:53.279
Please, I'll settle
for the lamest,

19:53.366 --> 19:55.803
most pathetic miracle you've
got lying around. Just...

19:55.890 --> 19:58.588
[Reese sobbing]

19:58.675 --> 20:00.111
[yelling]

20:00.199 --> 20:02.157
[whimpering]

20:07.554 --> 20:08.946
Well, I purposely dropped

20:09.033 --> 20:10.992
that bowling ball on your
foot so you couldn't go

20:11.079 --> 20:12.428
to your high school reunion!

20:12.515 --> 20:16.389
I'm two years older
than you think I am!

20:16.476 --> 20:17.955
Damn it, Hal,
we're reaching a point here

20:18.042 --> 20:20.001
I don't think either one of us
wants to get to!

20:20.088 --> 20:21.394
What are we supposed to do?!

20:21.481 --> 20:22.960
I've just got so much rage
built up...

20:23.047 --> 20:25.049
Are these your boys?

20:26.312 --> 20:28.662
You little monsters!

20:28.749 --> 20:30.272
How dare you get
into trouble again?!

20:30.359 --> 20:31.969
After all your mother
does for you!

20:32.056 --> 20:34.320
Your father slaves away
to put a roof over your head,

20:34.407 --> 20:35.756
and this is how
you repay him?!

20:35.843 --> 20:37.714
Okay, everybody,
let's just calm down...

20:37.801 --> 20:39.977
Why don't you mind
your own business?

20:40.064 --> 20:41.065
We don't need you

20:41.152 --> 20:42.502
coming in here and telling us

20:42.589 --> 20:43.938
how to handle our children.

20:44.025 --> 20:46.201
We know what we're doing.
Thank you very much.

20:46.288 --> 20:48.899
Mom, Dad, the drugs
are wearing off!

20:48.986 --> 20:50.901
[whimpering]

20:51.859 --> 20:53.164
Sundance, baby, is that you?

20:53.252 --> 20:54.514
[horse whinnies]

20:58.518 --> 21:00.215
[panting]

21:04.567 --> 21:07.483
Will you listen to me?!
I found you a job!

21:07.570 --> 21:09.572
-What?
-I found you a job!

21:09.659 --> 21:11.008
I've been trying to tell you.

21:11.095 --> 21:12.967
It's perfect for you!

21:13.054 --> 21:15.491
It's at the circus!

21:17.014 --> 21:19.147
The circus?

21:19.234 --> 21:22.106
In what world do you depreciate

21:22.193 --> 21:24.935
an elephant over two years?!

21:25.022 --> 21:26.894
I want this all
redone tonight!

21:28.025 --> 21:29.592
What are you looking at?

21:29.679 --> 21:31.942
Get back to work!

21:32.029 --> 21:34.510
HAL: That is
fantastic, son!

21:34.597 --> 21:37.078
Reese's roommate in
detox is a lawyer.

21:37.165 --> 21:39.994
He thinks he can blackmail him
into defending his felony case!

21:40.081 --> 21:41.561
That's great.

21:41.648 --> 21:43.998
Hey, the feeling's coming back
to my thighs.

21:44.085 --> 21:46.348
Apparently, the medical term
for what happened to me is

21:46.435 --> 21:47.915
"Holy crap, come look at this,"

21:48.002 --> 21:50.134
because that's all
the ER guys kept saying.

21:50.221 --> 21:51.571
But if I ever have
to give birth,

21:51.658 --> 21:53.050
it'll be really easy.

21:53.137 --> 21:55.226
And Mom seems
to be in a good mood lately.

21:55.314 --> 21:56.619
DEWEY: The toilet's
backed up again!

21:56.706 --> 21:57.968
I'll get it.

22:02.886 --> 22:05.628
[heels clopping]

22:43.449 --> 22:45.886
Captioned by Post Haste Digital
